http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/kerala/Vimochana-Yatra-begins-tomorrow/article14006251.ece

: In a bid to reinvigorate the party machinery ahead of the coming Assembly polls, Bharatiya Janata Party (BJP) State president Kummanam Rajasekharan will set off on a Statewide march from Uppala, near here, on Wednesday.The march, Vimochana Yatra, will be flagged off by Union Minister for Urban Development M. Venkaiah Naidu. The march will highlight the issues of food, drinking water, land, employment, and justice for all. It would pass through all 140 Assembly segments in the State and culminate at Parassala in Thiruvananthapuram on February 10, State party spokesman V.K. Sajeevan told a press conference here on Monday.He said the BJP would underscore the need to free the State from the clutches of the LDF and UDF alliances and highlight the development projects initiated in Kerala by the Narendra Modi-led government.The BJP State president will interact with leading social and cultural activists and enlist members in the BJP who were prepared to desert the LDF and UDF camps.